data.title: WOW!
data.text:
Was in town for Maroon 5 concert and went there for dinner!  My sushi (spicy tuna) roll was fresh and tasty!  Also ordered Sexy Salad (cucumber salad with some tuna on it) and it was very good!  My kid loved the Shrimp Sumai and egg rolls.
My other kid loved the Sumo soup!  One of the best soup he's had!  Boy, I wish there was one in NC!  Do not miss this place!

data.title: Great Food & Friendly Staff
data.text: TakoSushi is a very comfortable lunch time dining experience.  The Sushi and sashimi is very good. The staff is friendly and they make sure you are well taken care of.

data.title: Amazing sushi...well worth the drive!
data.text: It was my first time visiting Columbia to meet a friend for sushi. I solely went off of other reviews and very happy the I chose Takosushi. The food, atmosphere, service and location were all great! The place was hopping for dinner on a Saturday night but we got sat right away. They have a very extensive menu with a lot of great choices depending on what you're in the mood for. The Edamame, Rainbow, Super Krunchy and Spicy Tuna Rolls were all a hit and very fresh. Next time I visit Columbia I will definitely be making a stop at Takosushi. Well worth the hour drive!

data.title: Yummy
data.text:
My husband & I ate here on a recent trip through town. This restaraunt is mostly Japanese, but also offers Mexican style dishes, like quesadillas & tacos...hence the name Tako-Sushi.
We got the Firecracker, Spicy Salmon, & Tempura Shirmp rolls, plus Edamame. The edamame was really good & seasoned well. All the rolls were great & had a good balance of fish/other ingredients. My only issue was that they closed at 11 & the kitchen closed at that exact time. I wanted to order an additional Firecracker roll (because it was so good!) around 11:05 & the chef had already left the building & the kitchen had already closed. I was disappointed, but they did give me some sticky rice at no charge to make up for it.

data.title: Excellent Fusion Food!
data.text:
The sushi was amazing:  Crazy Susan (a favorite), Lobster rool and crazy roll with the Spicy shrimp.  The food is so good and tasty.  The spices blend so nicely with the protein and the tastes explode in your mouth.  The chef is very talented!

This is our 3rd visit to Takosushi.  Today is Memorial Day the restaurant business is down.  We were among 2 other couples in the restaurant and the service was fantastic!

data.title: Business as usual.
data.text: It was a good visit. Good quality fish and rolls are made on the spot. Unfortunately they use imitation crab meat (I recognize a lot of places do however). A little expensive given that it's collision SC. Good variety, but nothing special per se. Didn't really quench need for sushi.

data.title: Dinner with my daughter
data.text: Excellent service, free koozie, diverse and delicious menu items. This was my second time there and was not disappointed. Ate sushi and a local craft beer. Wonderful!

data.title: The best sushi I've had in Columbia
data.text: Wow!  This was quite the sushi experience!  I really enjoyed this place and pinched my arm for not coming in earlier.  I have passed this location hundreds of times, but never swung in to eat.  I will eat here more often for sure!  I found the sushi to have a significant amount of sushi.  Most sushi I have experienced had more rice than sushi, but not here.  They also had a few SC brewery beers I enjoyed immensely.

data.title: Great food
data.text: Everything we ordered on the menu from appetizer to main course was absolutely delicious! Ordered a little bit of everything off of the menu and it was definitely worth it. Will absolutely be eating here again next time visiting the area!

data.title: Great
data.text: Second trip and food was great, we were short on time an they got us in and out when very crowded.  One of the better sushi restaurants in Columbia.

data.title: Great Happy Hour Specials
data.text: They have a variety of specials during happy hour. My personal favorite is the tempura Asparagus. On the regular menu its the Crazy Susan !!! This is one of my favorite places to get in my meeee time. Even though I am not a drinker, I sit at the bar and watch the Big Screens while indulging in some good eats.

data.title: Tacos & Sushi Together? They make it work!!!
data.text:
When I first thought of having Tacos and Sushi together I thought it could never work... TakoSushi proved me wrong...

This very modern restaurant combines two great foods together in a harmonic blend. Very impressive and very delicious! 

Try their Shrimp Tacos and California Rolls... you'll thank me :)

data.title: Excellent
data.text:
I'm a big fan of sushi and now, thanks to takosushi, sashimi too.

Have been twice now for dinner and both times it was excellent  food.

Very cool atmosphere. 

Wait staff is hit or miss.

Will be my new sushi spot.

data.title: Crazy Susan!
data.text:
We visited after State Museum tour.  The food is excellent!   Firecracker shrimp, crazy Susan, Alaskan and Tempura Shrimp sushi.

The staff are eclectic and friendly.
The food amazing!

data.title: THE lunch place when in capital
data.text: Whenever we make the trip to Ft. Jackson we ALWAYS end our trip with Takosushi!  We usually get there right after the lunch crowd which is kool kause there is never a wait for a table, service or food. Full bar, great selection of drinks and beers; both bottles and on tap.  The menu is awesome! We always get different appetizers to share and my wife loves the crab chopchop...I always get the sashimi.  From the soup to the salads to the entres all is worth making the trip for and coming back to.  Solid 4 out of 5

data.title: Good sushi/food, service not so much
data.text:
However, I have to justify my title by saying it was VERY very busy the evening we went. That being said, it seemed like our server was spread far too thin, but did attempt to do his best. 

Party of 7 on a quite busy evening around 8. Although we were seated pretty quickly, drink order took quite some time (about a half hour....) and although we ordered as soon as drinks arrived, food to table was considerably longer. Server forgetting my saki (twice) was annoying, despite his apologies. 

When the food finally came, it was really quite good, the group ordered a variety of sushi/sashimi/rolls/appetizers which were shared around the table. Everything was tasty, and some of the house specialty rolls were interesting in their composition. 

I should note that for a facility that seats likely 30 tables, having only 3 chefs preparing food (at the sushi bar) seemed very inadequate. 

Would have given them four stars, but wait times and service mistakes took one away.

data.title: Awesome selection
data.text: This is the best of both worlds Mexican and sushi with a nice large menu to choose from. Small place can get crowded, and don't be surprised if you have to wait for food, but from the starters to the entrees the food is worth the wait I had the Dynamite and Pyramid rolls they were great. The variety of nachos is awesome as well

data.title: Amazafulistic food
data.text:
We visited on a Friday night.  The food was great!  The sushi: crazy Susan was absolutely yummy!  I ordered chicken stir fry dish and it was so good.  Mu husband ordered shrimp, scallops and noodles- very tasty!
No MSG or other additives to make you sick.  The atmosphere was cozy, upbeat.  The service was excellent!   The martinis are awesome!

data.title: Lunch in Columbia
data.text: Had a great lunch. Service was very good, but what was especially unique was the menu. I had the guacamole with blackened trout. Everything was delicious.

data.title: Great, Fresh People, Superb Food
data.text:
as we visited this hip restaurant with a group of six we´d really greta food. each of us had different Sushi, Seafood aor Mexican style. All of them were very well. I has Sushi and do Sushi also by myself. Only a very few times in lifetime I had this quality and taste.Even rare Tamago in a superb quality is excellent.
Very friendly service, greta selection of different beers, nice selection of wine. I do not know if they have been awarded already, but they should apply for it, they will definitely get an award. Easy to get there (next to the State Capitol).
Good mixture of gueast, young people, boomers, middle class people not over-the-top. Good place to be with freinds or as a couple.
